# RAG Studio — Cursor AI Rules

## Mandatory quality gates
Every file you create or edit MUST pass its linter/formatter before you consider
the task done. Do not mark work complete if lint errors remain.

---

## Python (apps/api)

- Formatter: `ruff format` (double quotes, 100-char lines, space indent)
- Linter:    `ruff check --fix` (rule sets: E W F I B C4 UP N S T20)
- Types:     `mypy` — every public function MUST have type annotations
- Run after edits: `cd apps/api && uv run ruff check --fix <file> && uv run ruff format <file>`
- NEVER use `pip` — always `uv pip install` or add to `requirements.txt`/`requirements-dev.txt`
- NEVER use `python -m venv` — `uv` manages the virtual environment
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → first-party (`app`) — `isort` via ruff `I` rules enforces this

### Common ruff fixes to apply proactively
- Remove unused imports (F401)
- Replace `Union[X, Y]` with `X | Y`, `Optional[X]` with `X | None` (UP007)
- Use f-strings instead of `.format()` (UP032)
- Remove `print()` statements; use `structlog` (T201)
- Use comprehensions instead of map/filter (C4)

---

## TypeScript / React (apps/web)

- Formatter: Prettier (`printWidth: 100, singleQuote: true, trailingComma: "all"`)
- Linter:    ESLint `next/core-web-vitals` + `prettier` (zero warnings allowed in CI)
- Types:     TypeScript strict — no `any` unless unavoidable; use `unknown` + type-guard instead
- Run after edits: `cd apps/web && npx prettier --write <file> && npx next lint --fix`

### React patterns to enforce
- Always use `const` arrow functions for components: `const MyComp = () => ...`
- Props interfaces: `interface MyCompProps { ... }` above the component
- No inline `style={{}}` — use Tailwind utility classes
- Memoize expensive renders: `useMemo`/`useCallback` when deps are stable
- Always handle loading/error states in async components
- `useSearchParams()` MUST be inside a component wrapped with `<Suspense>`

---

## Both languages
- No debug/stray `console.log` or `print()` in committed code
- No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials — use env vars
- No `// TODO` comments without a linked task reference
- Commit messages: imperative mood, ≤72 chars subject line
- Line endings: LF only (enforced by `.gitattributes`)
